# Current code

ent cli calls one of these two functions to access the db:
    ```
    fn make_issues_database(
        issues_database_source: &IssuesDatabaseSource,
        access_type: IssuesDatabaseAccess,
    ) -> Result<IssuesDatabase, Error>
    ```
        Make a long-lived IssuesDatabase by checking the db ref out into
        an ephemeral worktree, either in detached mode (for RO access)
        or in normal mode (for RW access).


    ```
    entomologist::database::read_issues_database(
        issues_database_source: &IssuesDatabaseSource,
    ) -> Result<crate::issues::Issues, Error>
    ```
        Call `make_issues_database` to make an RO checkout, read Issues
        from it, then close (throw away) the db.
